issue.body:
ES6 classes treat member functions as non-enumerable in the instantiated class. However remote currently only works with enumerable properties, which means I have to use the old school prototype style to define classes for remote use. I find it a little bit inconvenient.

Here is an example:

in main process
```
class ClientSocket {
    connect() {
        //..
    }
}
app.clientSocket = new ClientSocket();
```

in render process
```
const clientSocket = remote.app.clientSocket;
clientSocket.connect() // this doesn't work because connect() is not enumerable.
```

I mostly write new code in ES6 style and I'd like to keep my code style consistent. Is there any way to enable remote for ES6 class?

